Kim Jong Il Highly Praised in Brazil 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 12 (KCNA) -- The Brazilï¿½|Korea Friendship Association published a special issue of information bulletin titled "General Kim Jong Il, Great Defender of Socialist Cause" on Feb. 3 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 The bulletin said in an article that leader Kim Jong Il authored famous works "The Historical Lesson in Building Socialism and the General Line of Our Party" and "Socialism Is a Science", providing ideological and theoretical guidelines for upholding the socialist idea and reviving socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that the Pyongyang Declaration "Let Us Defend and Advance the Socialist Cause" adopted in April, 1992 was a historical document that saved the world socialist movement and put it on a new road of development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il decisively frustrated the vicious moves of the U.S. to destroy socialism and isolate and stifle the DPRK and firmly defended its socialism with his Songun politics, showing with a practical example which way the countries and peoples aspiring after socialism should follow to defend socialism, it stressed.

Struggle for Withdrawal of U.S. Forces Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 12 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity of south Korea in a special statement on February 7 declared it would concentrate all forces on the struggle against the U.S. and war and for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea, the action for smashing the U.S. war moves and driving the U.S. forces, the root cause of war, out of the land.
 The statement demanding a stop to the expansion of the U.S. forces' base in Phyongthaek charged that the U.S. military strategy on the Korean Peninsula is aimed at developing the U.S. forces in south Korea into "rapid task forces" and expanding their bases in line with their "strategic flexibility" in a bid to secure a base for mounting a preemptive attack on the north with ease. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unchangeable ambition of the U.S. to bring the inter-Korean relations to a collapse, perpetuate the presence of the U.S. forces in south Korea and put the Korean Peninsula under its control by availing itself of a good chance, it noted, and went on:
 If we allow the U.S. to block national reunification, we will become permanent slaves of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key to ensuring peace on the Korean Peninsula and in the rest of Asia lies in forcing the U.S. forces in south Korea to quit there at once to the last man.

Secretary of Libyan People's Bureau Here Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 12 (KCNA) -- Secretary of the People's Bureau of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya here Bashir Ramadan Khalifa Abu Janah hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Feb. 11 on the occasion of leader Kim Jong Il's birthday.
 The secretary in a speech made at the reception said that Kim Jong Il was born in Mt. Paektu and grew up hearing the gunfire during the anti-Japanese war, adding that he has performed immortal feats on behalf of the times and history while leading the Korean revolution for the past more than four decades.  Recalling that Kim Jong Il is providing ceaseless on-site guidance to various units to build a great prosperous powerful nation, he continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly and cooperative relations between Libya and the DPRK provided by Colonel Moammer el Gaddafi and President   Kim Il Sung have steadily developed under the deep concern of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the hope that the Korean people would register bigger success in building a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il and that the long-standing friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger and develop under the care of the leaders of the two countries.
 Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, noted in his speech that the long-standing friendly relations between the DPRK and Libya have steadily developed despite the present complicated international situation, adding that the Libyan people have extended invariable support and solidarity to the Koreans in their struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea under the Songun leadership of  Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people support the Libyan people in their efforts to achieve the independent progress and prosperity of the country under the leadership of Colonel Moammer el Gaddafi and will continue to boost the ties of friendship and cooperation with the Libyan people in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, Minister of Public Health Kim Su Hak, Chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea Ryom Sun Gil who is chairman of the DPRK-Libya Friendship Association and other officials concerned.

February Holiday Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 12 (KCNA) -- Seminars on the Juche idea were held in France, Thailand and Bangladesh in the period from Jan. 31 to Feb. 4 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 Jean Marie Lambret, chief of the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea, referred to the fact that leader Kim Jong Il declared the programme for modeling the whole society on the Juche idea 32 years ago, adding that the immortal Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung is the revolutionary one for achieving the independence of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He explained in detail the socio-historical principle of the Juche idea.
 Songchit Pullarp, chairman of the Organization for the Study of the Juche Idea of Thailand, pointed to the undying feats performed by Kim Jong Il in the struggle to accomplish the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Garib Newaz, president of the Bangladesh People's League, and other speakers said that the Juche idea is an outstanding guiding idea in the era of independence as it indicates the most correct road to be followed by humankind.  Referring to the reality of Korea where a protracted struggle to embody the Juche idea culminated in building a genuine popular regime which made the popular masses the master of the country and let everything serve them, he noted that this dream-like reality can hardly be found in any other part of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a seminar held in France.

February Holiday Celebrated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- Functions were held in different countries in the period from Jan. 28 to Feb. 3 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 Seminars on the feats of leader Kim Jong Il were held by the Communist Party of Tajikistan, the Workers' Party of Bangladesh and the Bulgariaï¿½|Korea Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the seminars the chairman of the Communist Party of Tajikistan and other speakers referred to the great contributions made by Kim Jong Il to the history of human thought, noting that such a great man as him who has performed distinguished exploits on behalf of humankind is rare to be found in other countries. 
 The Korean people have firmly defended and advanced socialism despite the imperialists' evermore undisguised moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK, entirely thanks to the Songun politics and Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The energetic diplomatic work conducted by Kim Jong Il with heads of state and political figures of different countries in recent years has made a distinguished contribution to establishing international relations in the new era, a just international order, they pointed out, stressing that the global cause of independence against imperialism will make a long drive following up victory thanks to his guidance.
 Reading sessions on "Short Biography of Comrade Kim Jong Il" were held by the Fasilï¿½|Rakwon Pharmacy Joint Company of Nigeria and the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea in Democratic Congo and lectures were arranged by the Congolese Socialist Party, the Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea of Democratic Congo and the Nigeriaï¿½|Korea Printing Industry Company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea of Democratic Congo introduced the great successes made by the Korean people in various fields in recent years thanks to the great Songun politics and highly praised Kim Jong Il as a great thinker and theoretician representing the present era.

International Meeting of Coordinators Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- A coordinators' meeting of the International Solidarity Council for Demanding Japan's Liquidation of the Past was held in Shanghai on Feb. 3.
 Present there were representatives of organizations affiliated with the council from Korea, China, Japan, Philippines, Netherlands, the U.S. and other countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting reviewed the activities of organizations in different countries and regions after the 3rd meeting of the council was held in Pyongyang in September last year and discussed the issues concerning work for this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It decided to further strengthen international solidarity activities for demanding Japan's liquidation of the past, now that the Japanese authorities have not taken any practical measure for liquidating Japan's past though 60 years have passed since its defeat but rather have more openly taken a retrogressive stand. 
 The meeting stressed that it would hold the 4th meeting of the council in Philippines late in July and continue to direct great efforts to the work of expanding the ranks including the work of involving organizations of damaged countries of Southeast Asia in the international solidarity activities for demanding Japan's liquidation of the past.

Study Tour of Native Home in Secret Camp on Mt. Paektu
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samjiyon, February 10 (KCNA) -- School youth and children from across the country made a study tour of the old home of leader Kim Jong Il in the secret camp on Mt. Paektu on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday.
 They left Hyesan on Feb. 4 and inspected the revolutionary battle sites and historic sites in the area of Mt. Paektu including Pochonbo, Phothae, Rimyongsu, Chong Hill and the secret camp on Mt. Paektu associated with the immortal traces of the three generals of Mt. Paektu till Feb. 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During their tour they held a question-and-answer study contest, a prompt report publishing contest, a procession chorus contest of revolutionary songs and other political and cultural work to acquire the revolutionary history, greatness and undying exploits of the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They arrived in Samjiyon on Thursday and laid floral baskets and bouquets before the statue of President Kim Il Sung standing on the side of the Lake Samji before making a bow in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round the Samjiyon Grand Monument.

Kimjongilia Exhibition of Ministry of People's Armed Forces Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- A Kimjongilia exhibition of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces was opened on the occasion of the significant holiday of February.
 On display were Kimjongilias put in full bloom by officials and employees of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Greenhouse of the ministry and servicepersons, officials, teachers, students and employees of Kim Il Sung Political University, the April 25 House of Culture and the Pak Myong Hun-led unit of the Korean People's Army and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony was held on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA General Pak Jae Gyong said in an opening address that each Kimjongilia carries the boundless loyalty of servicepersons keen to uphold the Songun revolutionary leadership of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il with loyalty who is successfully carrying forward the revolutionary cause of Juche, breaking through manifold difficulties and ordeals in the van with his stern stamina and pluck of Paektu.
 The participants looked round Kimjongilias on show.

Demonstration of S. Korean Moviemen
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- South Korean moviemen have reportedly staged demonstrations in protest against the pro-American sycophantic move of the authorities to cut down the screen quota of films.
 They held one-man demonstrations on Feb. 4 and 5 and cinema actor Jang Tong Gon staged a demonstration in front of the building of the "National Assembly" in Seoul on Feb. 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He insisted on keeping the screen quota, deploring that there would be no time to show whatever successful local films and the failure to maintain the screen quota would lead to the disappearance of the indigenous films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many passersby positively encouraged him in his demonstration condemning the pro-American humiliating act of the authorities, shouting slogan "Defence of Films!"

KCNA Blasts U.S. Gimmick to Evade Responsibility for Deadlocked Talks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- The United States is now busy floating fictions of "smuggling of fake cigarettes" and "smuggling of drugs" in a bid to achieve a sinister purpose, not content with peddling the lie about "counterfeit notes."
 Shortly ago, a White House spokesman blustered that the U.S. would never tolerate north Korea's involvement in illegal activities, referring to the reports of American newspapers to the effect that "fake cigarettes" made in north Korea are on sale in American markets.
 Meanwhile, the U.S. secretary of defense said that the prospect of the resumption of the six-party talks remains gloomy because the DPRK is acting against the U.S. financial sanctions, uttering that counterfeit notes, drug smuggling and sale of missile technology are north Korea's main source of revenue. 
 Underlying these outbursts is the U.S. foolish and mean attempt to tarnish the international image of the DPRK and shift the responsibility for the stalled six-party talks on to it at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the U.S. conservative hard-liners seek is to delay the six-party talks under any pretext, escalate the tension on the Korean Peninsula and thus draw water to its mill to meet its own political interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They fabricated something new and deliberately created an obstacle to the talks prompted by such way of thinking whenever there was a sign of their progress.
 They cooked up the story of "counterfeit notes" and kicked up the row for sanctions against their dialogue partner even before the ink got dry on the joint statement adopted at the fourth round of the six-party talks, spoiling the atmosphere of the talks.
 The Bush administration held a briefing on the "counterfeit notes" of the DPRK in Washington last December but failed to produce any clear evidence. This proved that it was nothing but a farce. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a true nature peculiar to the U.S. to spread sheer lies and interfere in the internal affairs of other countries and realize its attempt at aggression on their basis.
 A clear proof of this was the brigandish armed invasion launched by the Bush administration against Iraq on the basis of its false information. 
 That was why the unbiased international public opinion dismissed the stories about "smuggling of fake cigarettes" and "drug smuggling" and the like spread by U.S. media as a stereo-typed lie faked up by the U.S. ruling quarters and is demanding the U.S. immediately lift sanctions against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. gimmick to mislead the public opinion by spreading more lies while defying such demand will never convince the international community.

National Art Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- A national art exhibition to celebrate February 16 was opened.
 Put on display at the exhibition hall are more than 50 pieces of art works listed as national treasures including those showing the personalities of the three generals of Mt. Paektu as peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are oil painting "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung and anti-Japanese war hero Comrade Kim Jong Suk enjoying sunrise over Mt. Paektu" and Korean painting "On top of Mt. Paektu." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They impressively depict the immortal exploits of President Kim Il Sung, who made great contributions to the times, the revolution, the country and the people by making a history and traditions of steady victories and successfully solving the issue of succession to the leadership in carrying out the revolutionary cause of Juche, and the noble revolutionary life of Kim Jong Suk, who devoted her all to the cause of liberating the country by making a long journey of bloody anti-Japanese battles and gave a steady continuity to the traditions of the Korean revolution by giving birth to Kim Jong Il, a bright star over Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display in the hall are Korean painting "Blizzard on Mt. Paektu", "Leaving Giant Footprints for Songun Leadership", "Praising Our Soldiers' Singing as Best" and "Blue Sky over My Country" and other works dealing with the noble personality of leader Kim Jong Il as a great man making ceaseless inspections of the front and providing endless on-site guidance to different units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Drawing the eyes of visitors are works of various genres such as sculpture "I am a young man of liberated Korea" reflecting the unshakable faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to share their destiny with the headquarters of the revolution to the last, rallied close around  Kim Jong Il, Korean paintings "Ullim Falls" and "Beads Falls" showing the beautiful scenery of Songun Korea and other works dealing with the Koreans' happy life and their desire for national reunification.
 An opening ceremony took place at the Korean Art Gallery on Feb. 1

Agricultural Workers Celebrate February Holiday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- A meeting of agricultural workers was held at the People's Palace of Culture Friday to celebrate the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea, made an address at the meeting to be followed by speeches of other officials of the union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers said that the birth of Kim Jong Il as a bright star over Mt. Paektu was a great auspicious event and great fortune for the Korean nation and a historic event which promised a rosy future of the revolutionary cause of Juche and paved a wide avenue for the country's prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the agricultural workers to become patriotic farmers in the Songun era who are making a positive contribution to speeding up the building of a great prosperous powerful nation true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 An art performance was given by participants in the 34th national art festival of agricultural workers there to celebrate Feb. 16 that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of different art groups raised the curtain with a narration and chorus "Glory to General Kim Jong Il." Their repertoire included colorful art pieces including chorus "Confetti of Best Wishes" and a female chorus "Military Jeep Runs for Front Far Away." The performers sang high praises of the undying leadership exploits Kim Jong Il has performed by exalting the dignity and honor of socialist Korea under the banner of Songun and opening up a new history of building a great prosperous powerful nation.
 Present at the events were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned, officials of the union and other agricultural workers.

RS. Observes Day of Iranian People's Victory in Islamic Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- February 11 marks the 27th anniversary of the victory the Iranian people won in the Islamic revolution by overthrowing the pro-U.S. dictatorial regime through a nationwide uprising.
 On this occasion Rodong Sinmun Saturday carries a signed article.
 Recalling the fact that the Iranian people have defended the gains of the Islamic revolution under the uplifted banner of independence against imperialism and advanced along the road chosen by them, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Iranian people's drive to carve out a new life is now facing the vicious obstruction of the imperialists to stifle the Islamic revolution in Iran. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and other Western forces are escalating their interference in the internal affairs of Iran and pressure upon it as never before, taking issue with its activities for the peaceful use of nuclear energy aiming at the socio-economic development of the country. Iran, however, is strongly reacting to them, not yielding to such moves.
 The Iranian president in a recent statement said that Iran would continue to maintain its line for acquiring nuclear technology for a peaceful purpose despite any threat and blackmail. Noting that international law and agreements have granted Iran the right to use nuclear technology for a peaceful purpose, he stated that Iran would never concede this right. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., much upset by Iran's tough stand, has become undisguised in revealing its attempt to invade Iran by force of arms. To cope with it, Iran is bolstering its military capability for self-defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The efforts of the Iranian government and people to defend the sovereignty of the country and national interests and develop economy and culture are commanding international support.
